<GUIClass name="JSSBaseMdiForm" id="8902e9ac-2b6e-474a-93c1-5bea731f8233">
    <superclass name="JSSBaseForm"/>
    <transient/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>This is a base MDI Frame which can be subclassed within application subschemas.

The form includes a feature whereby options can be stored in the client's
JADE Initialization File to control the state (i.e. maximized or normal) of
the MDI Frame window, and its child windows.  Note that the menus on this
form, for the user to set the state settings, will be overwritten when
menus are implemented on subclasses of this form, so if the resize settings
are required, the menus on this form will need to be replicated on the subclass.
___________________________________________________________________________

              P R O P R I E T A R Y   N O T I C E

